A 13-year-old boy has been arrested on suspicion of the sexual assault of a teenage girl and two women. The schoolboy has been held in police custody. Each alleged attack took place in Bracknell, Berkshire this month. Thames Valley Police confirmed yesterday they have arrested the 13-year-old following incidents on women in South Hill Park between July 5 and 6. A spokesperson said: ‘Following an investigation by Thames Valley Police, a boy has been arrested on suspicion of sexual assault. ‘The 13-year-old remains in police custody at this time. ‘His arrest is in relation to sexual assaults that happened in South Hill Park, Bracknell, on 5 July and 6 July in which a teenage girl and two women in their 20s were assaulted over their clothing in three separate incidents.’ The teenager, who is from Berkshire, has not been named. Get in touch with our news team by emailing us at webnews@metro.co.uk. For more stories like this, check our news page.